    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIt seems that I mentioned about on the sidelines of another main thread, but cannot find such one.\n\nI see that at the moment we can work the problem around by, f.e. `lua vim.wo[require('vim._extui.shared').wins.msg].winhl = 'Normal:Comment'` (wrapped by `vim.schedule` when called in a script just after enable `extui`) and the effect survives switching to another window ID after `:fclose!` (not checked why), but it would be nice to have a standard and reliable way to do it. \n\n### Expected behavior\n\nProbably we need to define some new builtin highlighting groups and use them for extui windows. The user (or colorscheme plugin creator) would then have only to redefine them. I'm not sure how much new groups we need - for my personal usage I need to redefine only `Normal` and `Search`.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
